Provided a fix. Basically it was changing the following code 

{code}
timeout = 0;
timeout = ncGetTimeout(op_start, timeout, (stop - start), i);
rc = ncClientCall(pMeta, timeout, resourceCacheLocal.resources[i].lockidx, resourceCacheLocal.resources[i].ncURL, "ncGetConsoleOutput", instanceId, consoleOutput);
{code}

to 

{code}
timeout = 0;
timeout = ncGetTimeout(op_start, OP_TIMEOUT, (stop - start), i);
rc = ncClientCall(pMeta, timeout, resourceCacheLocal.resources[i].lockidx, resourceCacheLocal.resources[i].ncURL, "ncGetConsoleOutput", instanceId, consoleOutput);
{code}

Talked with [~nurmi] and the last fix only patches the symptoms and not resolve the underlying problem. The real problem is that for the GetConsoleOutput operation only, the CLC does not like the following answer on failure:

{code}
<n:statusMessage>ERROR</n:statusMessage><n:return>false</n:return>
{code}

This error message cause the following problem in the CLC:

{code}
Tue Dec 18 16:18:41 2012  WARN [Binding:New I/O client worker #58825-1] [com.eucalyptus.binding.Binding.fromOM(Binding.java):289] org.jibx.runtime.JiBXException: E\
xpected "{http://eucalyptus.ucsb.edu/}consoleOutput" start tag, found "{http://eucalyptus.ucsb.edu/}GetConsoleOutputResponse" end tag (line -1, col -1, in SOAP-mes\
sage)
org.jibx.runtime.JiBXException: Expected "{http://eucalyptus.ucsb.edu/}consoleOutput" start tag, found "{http://eucalyptus.ucsb.edu/}GetConsoleOutputResponse" end \
tag (line -1, col -1, in SOAP-message)
{code}
